=== ANTAGONIST-SIDE OPERATIONAL FACETS ===

[ THE 137-YEAR PRINCEDOM AS INSTITUTIONAL WEIGHT: From 
  Anarch perspective, Lytton's continued Princedom is 
  137 years of accumulated Camarilla institutional 
  pressure on the continent. Every Anarch operational 
  decision in southeastern Australia has been shaped 
  partly by Lytton's continued authority; every 
  cross-sect arrangement has been negotiated under 
  Lytton's framework; every Camarilla-Anarch friction 
  has been resolved (or unresolved) under Lytton's 
  Princely judgement. From Anarch ideological perspective, 
  this is Camarilla institutional dominance perpetuated 
  by individual political longevity rather than 
  earned through ongoing political legitimacy. Red 
  Mag's 60-year unwritten accord with Lytton has 
  required her ongoing Anarch-internal political work 
  to maintain; some Anarchs (particularly younger 
  Brunswick-enclave Kindred, particularly Theo-Ramos-equivalent 
  radical-wing operatives) consider the accord 
  ideological compromise that should be ended through 
  Lytton's overthrow. ]

[ THE BECKONING-WEAKNESS AS OPERATIONAL OPPORTUNITY: 
  Lytton's three Beckoning episodes since 2018 represent 
  growing operational vulnerability that chronicle-active 
  forces (Sarrasine's Phase Two, Brisbane Sabbat 
  expansion considerations, Anarch radical-wing 
  succession-pressure, Hardacre's AFP-TP investigation) 
  can leverage. Lytton's resistance to the Beckoning 
  has been costly; his operational capacity has 
  measurably declined since 2018; his decision-making 
  has shown small hesitations that institutional 
  observers (Sister Fatima Salih-El, Tania Oberon, 
  Sofia Calabria-Hecata's family branch through 
  cross-faction observation) have privately tracked. 
  Sarrasine specifically has been adapting his Phase 
  Two timing to Lytton's Beckoning trajectory because 
  Lytton's eventual succumbing produces optimal 
  operational conditions for Sarrasine's continental 
  destabilisation. ]

[ THE CAMARILLA INSTITUTIONAL CONSERVATISM: Lytton's 
  ethical frame is conservative-Camarilla with Australian 
  informality. From Anarch perspective, the conservatism 
  is real and operationally consequential. Lytton has 
  declined three substantive opportunities across 137 
  years to formally extend Camarilla recognition to 
  Anarch territorial authority in southeastern Australia 
  (declined in 1962, 1989, 2024 centennial Cress Truce 
  renewal) on conservative-institutional grounds that 
  Anarchs read as Camarilla-orthodoxy-prioritisation 
  over operational pragmatism. Lytton's three declinations 
  have constrained Anarch Movement Australian political 
  development in ways that current Anarch theorists 
  consider documented operational damage rather than 
  merely ideological friction. ]

[ THE SUCCESSION-UNDECIDEDNESS: Lytton has been considering 
  succession (Octavia Marsh of Adelaide vs. Lumley vs. 
  contested Praxis) for two years and has not chosen. 
  The undecidedness is operational vulnerability — every 
  Australian Kindred political force is partly oriented 
  around the question without resolution. The undecidedness 
  also represents Lytton's prerogative-of-Princedom 
  exercised without institutional accountability mechanism; 
  Anarchs particularly read this as Camarilla institutional 
  failure to provide systematic succession protocols, 
  with the failure traceable to 137-year Princedom 
  stability that has not required succession exercise. ]

[ THE COURT-INFRASTRUCTURE-CONSOLIDATION: Lytton's 
  Toorak Circle is operational infrastructure of 
  significant capability; its institutional consolidation 
  produces Camarilla Melbourne dominance that Anarch 
  perspective considers structural-political rather 
  than meritocratic. Sister Fatima as Sheriff, Tania 
  Oberon as Harpy, Galileo Trevelyan as Keeper of 
  Elysium, Lumley as Seneschal-equivalent: every senior 
  Camarilla institutional position is held by Lytton's 
  selected operatives, which reflects Princely competence 
  in selection but also structural-political-arrangement 
  that Anarch institutional analysis considers 
  consolidation-of-power-by-selection rather than 
  consolidation-of-power-by-capability. The distinction 
  is partially semantic and partially operationally 
  consequential. ]

[ THE BATH-FORMAL CULTURAL POSITION: Lytton's 
